@meta
title: {{TITLE}}
version: {{VERSION}}
owner: {{OWNER}}

@map
- PM-001 | Incident Summary | Summarize timeline and impact
- PM-010 | Timeline | Record key events from detection to recovery
- PM-015 | Decision Chain and Assumptions | Reconstruct key decisions and assumptions
- PM-020 | Root Cause Analysis | Separate direct and root causes
- PM-030 | Response Review | Capture what worked and what failed
- PM-040 | Prevention Actions | Define concrete follow-up actions
- PM-050 | Source Feedback Completion | Ensure postmortem results are reflected in source docs

@section PM-001
title: Incident Summary
summary: Record incident duration and user impact in one place
links: INCIDENT-001
content:
<<<
[Incident window]
- Start:
- End:

[Impact]
- User-facing impact:
- Estimated affected users:
>>>

@section PM-010
title: Timeline
summary: Keep high-signal, time-ordered event history
links: LOG-001
content:
<<<
00:00 - First alert
00:00 - On-call acknowledged
00:00 - Investigation started
00:00 - Mitigation applied
00:00 - Recovery confirmed
>>>

@section PM-015
title: Decision Chain and Assumptions
summary: Restore why key decisions were made and what assumptions were used
links: DECISION-TRACE-001
content:
<<<
[Key decisions]
1) Decision:
   - Assumption:
   - Evidence at the time:
   - Approver:

[Assumptions that failed]
1)
2)
>>>

@section PM-020
title: Root Cause Analysis
summary: Focus on causes, not only symptoms
links: PR-001
content:
<<<
[Direct cause]
1)
2)

[Root cause]
1)
2)

[Missed signals]
- Early warning:
- Test gap:
>>>

@section PM-030
title: Response Review
summary: Keep balanced review for team learning
links: RETRO-001
content:
<<<
[What went well]
1)
2)

[Needs improvement]
1)
2)
>>>

@section PM-040
title: Prevention Actions
summary: Define owner and due date for each action item
links: ACTION-BOARD-001
content:
<<<
1) Action: / Owner: / Due:
2) Action: / Owner: / Due:
3) Action: / Owner: / Due:
>>>

@section PM-050
title: Source Feedback Completion
summary: Treat postmortem as complete only after source-doc updates are recorded
links: SOURCE-FEEDBACK-001
content:
<<<
[Source updates]
1) Source doc:
   - Updated section:
   - Change ID:
   - Owner:
   - Completed date:

[Completion gate]
- Postmortem status can be closed only when source update evidence exists
>>>

@change CHG-{{DATE}}-01
target: PM-040
date: {{DATE}}
author: {{OWNER}}
reason: Initial template scaffolding
impact: Replace with incident-specific evidence and actions
